args:
Having seen her brother's growth firsthand,
Louise becomes determined to let him go.
But at that moment, Garuda appears and
things get heated. However, fiends attack
the nearby village, forcing both party and
dragon to work together to defeat them.
The village isn't far now, but I'm worried\nabout how many more fiends we've seen\nsince entering these woods.
I feel like there are even more than before.\nPerhaps it's because Garuda isn't around.
Hrraaagh! That takes care of that one.\nThink that was all of 'em?
Looks like it. Let's keep goin—
(It's too fast—I won't have time to take it\nout with my bow.)
Louise! Lowen! Are you two okay?!
Hot damn, kid! You jumped right into the\nthick of it, didn't ya?!
I couldn't just stand there and let it get\nmy sister. I had to do something.
And yeah, I was scared, but I wasn't going\nto let that stop me!
You did a great job, Lowen.
He saved you, Louise. Plain and simple.
You've grown into a splendid young man,\nLowen. And I'm sure Louise knows that,\neven if she won't say it.
I'm sorry, Lowen. I just couldn't say\nanything because... Well, because\nI am terrifically sad.
If you told me you didn't need me\nanymore, I... I'd have nothing.
You HAVE become such a fine young man,\nand yet all I can do is think about myself.\nI don't deserve you for a brother.
Oh my gosh, that is SO not true!
Without you, I'd have been dead a looong\ntime before this!
I'm so grateful to you, and yet there's\nnever been anything I could do FOR you.
But now it's different, because I'm strong\nenough to protect YOU!
I want to make you happy, Louise—and I\nwant you to find your own happiness, too.
You're all the family I have left, and you're\nso important to me.
Louise, you have a brother who's grown\ninto a fine young man.
Can you really say you'll ＂have nothing＂\nwhen you have him?
No... You're right. I should have realized\nthat much sooner.
But I suppose I can start with today.
Lowen, thank you for protecting me.\n...You've truly grown up.
Well then! Have you finally gained the\nresolve to part with your brother?
What are we gonna do?! We haven't been\nable to talk to the villagers OR take out\nthe fiends yet!
If she takes Lowen here, we won't have\nanything to negotiate with.
Whatever are you whispering about there?\nCome now, the time for play is over.
Hand the boy over or face my wrath.
What are we going to do?
Hey, Garuda! Wait! Are you really—
That scream came from the village!
Fiends attacking the village? Have I truly\nneglected my duties so...?
Garuda, after this, I promise I'll do\nanything you say!
So please, right now, let me go save\nthe village!
Go then! I will help you drive them back!
